The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 2: Sebi has issued a new directive under which retail and institutional investors will be treated alike while bidding for shares in public offers. The move is likely to bring down the exorbitant levels of over subscriptions in the primary market. The directive will come into effect from tomorrow. Institutions will now have to pay upfront 100 per cent money in primary issues like the retail investors.                             
	 New Delhi, May 2: Industry expects the economy to grow 7.5-8.5 per cent during the current fiscal, fuelled mainly by rising capital investment and expanding exports, a CII survey has said. Majority (of respondents) expects economic growth to be in the 7.5-8.5 per cent range, said the CII Business Outlook Survey.                            
	 New Delhi, May 2: Leading pharmaceutical companies such as Cipla, Ranbaxy, Pfizer and Dr Reddys are among the firms pulled up by drug price regulator National Pharmaceuticals Pricing Authority for overcharging.                            
	 Hyderabad, May 2: Insurance regulator IRDA has directed New Delhi-based Radiant Overseas to stop selling insurance policies of a Ukraine insurer as they are not registered with the sectoral watchdog.                            
	 Mumbai, May 2: Max Bupa Health Insurance plans to infuse around Rs 550 crore in the next five years, Max Bupa Health chief executive Damien Marmion said. The companys present paid-up capital is Rs 151 crore.                                                                                                                          
